The food was ok. They stole my money. MUST READ!!! I went to this restaurant this past Sunday the 31st of May 2020. My order cost a total of 15 dollars. I bought my friend meal too which was a separate order and her meal cost 18 dollars. So in total my meal cost 33 dollars. I checked my recent transactions and I noticed a charge of 56.00 dollars from this establishment. I called  the restaurant the owner asked if I had my receipt and I replied yes. He asked for the number on the top of the receipt and I gave it to him. He then replied and said yes I see a tip of 22.50 was added. I kindly said I did not write a tip of that amount. He told me that he will call his bank and refund me the 22.50. I then asked is he going to compensate me with anything else due to this circumstance. He said no. If I would have never checked my account they would have stole 22.50 from me. Better yet if I did not keep my receipt I would of been out of 22.50. This establishment steals people money so be careful and make sure you cross out the tip area in its entirety.  I will not be coming back to this establishment.

So this was my first time here. The service was great the people working there are very nice. Whoever is in charge though could have been more accommodating considering it was our first time here. We went there during happy hour by coincidence and they told us about the deal for half a pitcher that serves about 4 drinks for $12 and a full pitcher for $32. We didn’t hear him clearly; we had thought the pitcher was $32 overall and my husband didn’t want to drink that much so we just ordered 2 drinks at $5 each. When we did the math in my head before I started drinking I made my husband ask about the deal again and it was the half pitcher for $12 so I asked if we could have a half of the half pitcher extra making it a 4 drink serving since we had already ordered 2 single drinks and our waiter tried but they said no and the drinks were good so that was a loss for us over a simple misunderstanding. Then we ordered the chicken quesadillas that had the chicken shredded and it was great. It wasn’t the same as cubed chicken which tastes better to me. Then my husband order the chicken shrimp steak and pineapple entree and it came with rice and refríed beans I tried some of his food and it didn’t have much seasoning to taste and I could not for the life of me find a piece of pineapple or even taste it. The rice was old and the food overall was subpar. Btw I am Hispanic and for that being a “Mexican “ restaurant it was lacking a lot of taste. The drinks were good though !! Just listen to the deals well or make them repeat it so you don’t make the mistake we made.

Elora you have forever lost a customer....over 15 years of patronizing this establishment and suffering through the new owners changes to make it worse, well today is the day I stop giving my business to you. The level of customer service has continued to go down. The okay we are doing you a favor is beyond what i can take at this point. The food is okay but the drinks are what I enjoy the most. So as usual, I order a pitcher of margarita (watermelon not sweet- yes I want the manager to know who I am) my usually order. My and the person in with drinks come out looking like melted iced water. I mentioned to the waiter “what’s with the drinks they look like soup” he responds “oh the machine must be hot” I’m like huh?  So since i try to be an easy going customer, I stay with the drink. Well before I could finish my first glass, the pitcher looks and taste like warm rose colored water. i mention to the waiter that the drink is warm and can it be taken back to refreshen or give me the drink i actually asked for, “a pitcher of frozen watermelon margarita not too sweet”. He then goes off to what it appear like speak to the person behind the bar, then goes outside, and comes back and says nothing ...nothing until I call him over and inquire again about the drink. After calling him over and having an aimlessly conversation about the quality of the drink, the waiter saying there’s nothing he can do, so I request to speak to the manager. The manager, who’s been watching the entire exchange because he’s the person behind the bar, comes over and no acts completely obtuse to all that is happening. After I explained that the drink was soupy when it first arrived and that in all my years of coming i have never had a drink come lukewarm and that I’m not asking for anymore than I am I’m paying for and that is a FROZEN drink bc this was soupy and melted when I got it, he tells me oh you should have sent it back then. I sated the exchange between the waiter and I initially and the waiter response and the manager says oh well you did tell him to take it back.  (REALLY!!! Are you kidding  me you are making the drinks you knew this drink was unacceptable when you served it, I mentioned it to the waiter but because i didn’t say take it back - you do see the need to fix this.) so in my pleasant voice I again request a fresh drink. The manager then says using far too many hand gestures,  ok but if the the next one melts your not getting another because we already taking a lost. At that point, I determined and thought - “I will keep your subpar drink do me no favors because after this you will take the loss and never get my business again” I graciously said you know what let me keep this LAST drink, thank you I’m fine. Since I was with a friend who was hungry, I ordered the least expensive items on the menu keep the warm drink and officially cut my tides with this establishment. After 15 years of weekly to monthly visits, end of year parties, athletic celebrations, celebrating as staff move on from busboys to waiters, gave birth and even morn with them when those a wonderful waiter in death.... For many years I enjoyed coming here and recommending it to friends but no more ...in the last few years year prices have gone up while the quality of food and customer service has gone down ...it unfortunate that your failure to show good customer service is the reason you’ve lost a customer of many years

LOVE LOVE Elora's!! It's going to become a new "routine" place I have to stop on my visits toLOVE  new work. I went there with a friend and we had such an amazing time we ended up coming back later that night for coffee and dessert. In addition to the complementary chips and salsa we ordered the guacamole, which I happened to watch them hand make on my way to the bathroom (and which comes with wonderful corn tortillas in addition to chips), flautas al diablo, a side of rice and beans, and the black bean and cheese burrito (which also came with rice and beans). Somewhat ironically, given that I'm a carnivore, my favorite thing was actually what my vegetarian friend ordered, the bean and cheese burrito, and I could easily get two meals out of it even without apps/chips. All of the food was fresh, authentic, and the portions were extremely generous. We also got a half pitcher of frozen margaritas and my first horchata, both awesome. The staff of this multi-generational family-owned business are so friendly and welcoming. They even remembered my friend who had only been there a few times before. We found parking less than a block away for free on the street with no time limits. Outdoor shaded seating was perfect and it's on the cutest little corner. We saw lots of people walking their dogs and kids, very neighborly atmosphere. We came back at night for flan (my friend had never had it before!) and coffee, which were both fantastic. Can't wait to come back and try to the coconut flan next, and also their sister restaurant - El Viejo Yayo 2!
